1 (d) A voter shall specify in an absentee ballot application submitted in accordance
2 with subsection (b) of this section:
3 (1) one of the following methods by which the voter chooses to receive an
4 absentee ballot:
5 (i) mail;
6 (ii) facsimile transmission; or
7 (iii) the Internet; and
8 (2) one of the following methods by which the voter chooses to be contacted
9 by the State Board under subsection (g) of this section before each election:
10 (i) nonforwardable mail;
11 (ii) e–mail; or
12 (iii) text message.
13 (g) (1) [Not less than 75] DURING THE PERIOD BEGINNING 120 DAYS
14 BEFORE AN ELECTION AND ENDING 90 days before [the day on which a local board begins
15 to send absentee ballots to voters] THE ELECTION, the State Board shall send a written
16 communication to each voter who is on the permanent absentee ballot list [as of a date that
17 is at least 90 days before the upcoming election] using the method chosen by the voter
18 under subsection (d)(2) of this section.
19 (2) The communication required under paragraph (1) of this subsection
20 shall include:
21 (i) confirmation that the voter is included on the permanent
22 absentee ballot list;
23 (ii) the address of the voter;
24 (iii) the method by which the voter has chosen to receive an absentee
25 ballot; and
26 (iv) a statement that the voter must notify the local board if any of
27 the changes listed in subsection (j) of this section have occurred.
28 (3) If the State Board is unable to contact a voter using the method of
29 communication chosen by the voter under subsection (d)(2) of this section, the State Board
30 shall [send the written communication] ATTEMPT TO CONTACT THE VOTER using
31 another method [if the State Board has other contact information for the voter].

